text: Garsen, United States National Geospatial-Intelligence Agency is a small town in Tana River County, Kenya. It is on the west bank of the Tana River. ==Location== Garsen is located on the banks of the Tana River, in Tana River County, approximately south of Hola, the location of the county headquarters. It lies along the Malindi–Garissa Road, approximately north of Malindi. ==Overview== Garsen marks the western end of the Garsen–Witu–Lamu Highway. ==See also== *List of roads in Kenya ==References== ==External links== *Website of Tana River County Category:Populated places in Tana River County
title: Garsen
